text: Water Sprite , who desired , above all things , to obtain a human soul
a man , possessed already of a soul , and destined for immortality
a boy with long fair hair and a crimson cap
some one whom thou hast benefited
not a few who seemed to be weary of this life of many sorrows
some aged and want - worn creature who would do him the kindness he desired
those who must look forward to the fewest days and to the most misery
a certain young man in a boat upon the lake
a young maid who was his sweetheart
One who has watched the passing misfortunes of many generations before thine
a little old man wringing out his beard into the lake
the only stay of aged parents
one who pauses to hearken with cleft lips
a girl moved by some plaintive song , and the sun burst forth as if to see who made such sweet music
